{
  "text": "In anaesthesia for elective procedures, the \"6:4:2\" rule is followed, i.e. no intake of solid food and milk formula for at least 6 hours before anaesthesia, of mother's milk for 4 hours and of clear, non-carbonated fluids for 2 hours. Prolongation of fasting over the minimum requirements puts the children at risk of aspiration of low pH gastric contents [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
